{"id": 14472, "source": "pestle", "subject": "biology", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "3", "year": "2019", "session": "19N", "subtopic": "b-2-biotechnology-in-agriculture", "title": "19N.3.SL.TZ0.10", "topic_id": "b", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>A sequence of DNA is translated in a continuous reading frame without spaces. Each triplet of nucleotides corresponds to successive amino acids in a polypeptide. The sequence given shows part of one strand of a DNA molecule.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"/></p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Identify the first triplets of each possible reading frame for this piece of DNA.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Define what is meant by an open reading frame.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>AAT <strong>and</strong> ATG <strong>and</strong> TGC<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>ATG <strong>and</strong> TGC <strong>and</strong> GCG ✔</p>\n<p><em>All three triplets required</em>.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>a significant length of DNA that begins with a start codon and ends with a stop codon ✔</p>\n<p><em>Significant length or similar phrase required</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>"}